        <div class="msgSubject">Sword &amp; Board Guide : How to Tank without stamina issues</div>
        <div class="sm notbold">
          
          Posted: 2010-11-01 08:04:28 | Edited: Nov 01 2010  8:55am  | <input type="checkbox" name="quote-1288620268102778762" id="quote-1288620268102778762" class="msgQuoteCheck" onchange="multiQuote2()"/><label for="quote-1288620268102778762" onclick="multiQuote2()"> Quote</label>  | <a href="/forum.html?forum=175&amp;mid=1288620268102778762&amp;post=1&amp;replyto=1288620268102778762&amp;page=1" class="icon-replytothis" rel="nofollow">Reply to Post</a> | <a id="FOLLOW_MID_1288620268102778762" onclick="followToggle('add','1288620268102778762')" href="javascript:" class="icon-follow">Follow</a> 
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgWhoFrame">
        <div class="msgUM"><a class="msgWhoName Sage" href="/users/Skyfaller">Skyfaller</a><div class="msgWhoTitle Sage">Sage</div></div><div class="msgAvatar"></div><div class="msgStar"><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/></div><div class="msgWhoNum">66 posts</div>
        <div class="msgScore">
          Score: Good  
          <div class="msgRatings"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">Tanking is the art of keeping a target focused on you while at the same time being able to keep yourself alive through an effective defense. Inflicting damage on the target is of tertiary importance to the tank however it is still a requirement of the role. All these three things the Gladiator can do very effectively with <b>a low stamina cost.</b> <br /> <br /> <br />This is achieved by using a combination of abilities from other classes and using a Shield Fighting style. <br /> <br /> <br />Abilities you will need (listed by class and rank) <br /> <br />Pugilist <br /> <br />1. <b>Taunt (10)</b> - Focuses target on you. Short duration. <br />2. <b>Second Wind</b> - Heals you using TP. <br />2. <b>Jarring Strike (14)</b> - only after evading attack: Deals high damage and stuns target. <br /> <br />Marauder <br /> <br />1. Defender (10) - Increases defense for 1 minute. <br />2. <b>Fracture (14)</b> - TP WS that renders target incapable of using weaponskills. Can only be done after a Parry. <br />3. Disorient (18) - Lowers evasion and generates enmity. Stacks up to 3 times. <br /> <br />Conjurer: <br /> <br />1. Cure (4) or Cure II (20) - the higher your conjurer's rank and MND stats the better the cures.  <br />2. <b>Shock Spikes (8)</b> - Causes target to be stunned when it hits you. Lasts 5 minutes. <br />3. Protect (16) - Increases your defense for approximately 4 minutes. <br />4. Shell (16) - Increases magic defense for approcimately 4 minutes.  <br /> <br />Thaumaturge: <br /> <br />1. Slow (8) - Causes target stamina to regenerate slowly.  <br />2. Bio (12) - Lowers target defense, lowers target damage output.  <br />3. Absorb spells (18)- Absorb DEF and Absorb Evasion are excellent for a Tank. <br /> <br />Gladiator: <br /> <br />1. <b>Phalanx (8)</b> - Costs no stamina, deals high damage to target after a block.  <br />2. <b>Provoke (10)</b>- Focuses target on you. Short duration. <br />3. Heavy Slash (20) - Slash that generates enmity.  <br /> <br />Shield: <br /> <br />1. <b>Guard (1)</b> - Raises your shield. <br />2. Aegis Boon (10) - Converts blocked damage into HP for you.  <br />3. Shield Bash (14) - Slams target with shield dealing damage, may interrupt target's casting.  <br /> <br /> <br />Depending on your personal stats and preference you can mix and match from the above. Those highlighted in bold are MANDATORY to be able to execute the Shield Fighting Style. <br /> <br /> <br />Shield Fighting Style: <br /> <br />The basic function of this fighting style is to stay behind the cover of your shield and attack only with reactionary attacks (evade/parry/block) while generating constant enmity towards you (and keeping target focused on hitting your shield). <br /> <br />The method is simple: For every combat round (meaning every time the mob attacks) you attack up to a maximum of two times. Of those two attacks per combat round, one is either raise your shield again -or- do a reactionary attack (block/parry/evade) and the second can be either a reactionary attack or a non-tp using attack (light stab or heavy slash as both use very low stamina and zero tp) or a spell/taunt(or provoke) from the list above.  <br /> <br />Example of how this works: <br /> <br />Gladiator buffs himself, raises shield and attacks target. Provoke is used as the second attack in the first combat round.  <br /> <br />Mob attacks (1). since shield is up the shield always blocks.  <br /> <br />Gladiator does Phalanx then does Slow. <br /> <br />Mob attacks (2). Shield is up so it always blocks. <br /> <br />Gladiator does Phalanx then does Light Stab. TP is now around 400 <br /> <br />Mob attacks (3). Shield is up so it always blocks. Shield lowers a second after the third mob attack is blocked. <br /> <br />Gladiator raises shield again and does Phalanx.  <br /> <br />Mob attacks (4). Shield is up but gladiator EVADES the hit. <br /> <br />Gladiator does Jarring Strike. Target is Stunned. Gladiator does Defender and Provokes target (the stun gives you a couple more seconds before next combat round).  <br /> <br />and so on and one until the mob dies.  <br /> <br />This fighting technique ensures you will ALWAYS have almost full stamina, ensures you are taking full advantage of every defense available to the Gladiator and you are constantly generating heavy enmity via phalanx and spells (which have more enmity than regular light attacks) and keeps target focused on the gladiator at all times via provokes and taunts.  <br /> <br />Your damage output is relatively high. It does not compare to the spamming of light attacks and TP WS's but it is still very good damage.  <br /> <br />Better yet, this fighting style also gives you lots of shield skillups! <br /> <br />Parry and Evade instances, while not common as with other classes, do happen usually once every fight or two. When they happen you cannot use phalanx since shield did not block... and using the evade/parry reactionary strikes gives the gladiator not only damage output but an excellent status effect to inflict on target.  <br /> <br />Spells may be frowned upon by many but i've found them insanely useful to lower the damage output of a mob. Shock spikes practically lowers the incoming damage damage by 40% by stunning the mob half the time for half a combat round's worth of time. Bio lowers damage of mob by about 20%. Slow is great to toss onto a mob when it is near 50% hp as it can in many cases prevent them from spamming TP moves on you. All these spells generate great enmity towards you so its good thing.  <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />My personal recommendation for STATS for someone dedicated purely to Gladiator shield tanking is to focus on Vitality, Mind, Dex and Piety. Vitality and Dex the two highest priorities, Mind and Piety receiving = amount of points. Strength can be largely ignored as a tank is not a damage dealer... and with a mere 30 str you still hit targets for 120+ with phalanx (which is your bread and butter damage dealing attack in this fighting style). With high Vit and Dex you ensure your ability to stay alive through sheer HP and ability to land phalanx and other enmity-building strikes. Mind and Piety extend your MP pool, healing power and magic accuracy for the debuffs who'se job is to lower incoming damage (thus enhancing your survivability and enmity generation).   <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov  1st 2010 10:55am by Skyfaller </span></i></div>
