      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">BartelX wrote:</div><div class="orig">This was an extremely interesting read.  Personally, I use more of a light slash/WS build but I can definitely see the merit in this. </div></div> <br /> <br />The light slash/ws does not let you keep hate nor lowers the damage you take in. Sure, it works great vs blues and green but against yellows and reds the slash/ws can be suicidal. I was ranking up my gladiator from 1 to 12 with light slash/ws and holding shield up on orange Yarzons/Galagos when I started trying out the reactionary attacks.  <br /> <br />The difference was significant since I noticed that I would end fight with nearly full HP (having used 2nd wind only once) and full stamina bar. I could even tank 2 at a time and not sweat it (blocking 1 mob lets you Phalanx the other one lol!). The other day I had a red wolf, a yellow yarzon and an orange galago ganking me and I slammed them all down by killing the weakest (yarzon) then the galago then the wolf. I had stamina the whole way. If I had been slashing and stabbing the galago when the yarzon and wolf popped and aggroed me I would have had no stamina to do anything XD.  <br /> <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig"> <br />The one problem I could foresee is that using nothing but WS will kill a mob in a lot less hits and give out less total sp I believe.  I tend to spam Light Slash more as I've noticed that I get consistently more SP per mob by hitting as many times as possible. <br /> <br />In a group though, this sounds like a really great tanking style.</div></div> <br /> <br />Indeed this is mainly for groups (because it DOES hold hate perfectly) and for tanking oranges and reds when solo. for blues/green you can hack them as fast as you can.  <br /> <br />However it does not change the SP gain that much. Thing is, the SP you get is also tied to the damage you do. I almost always get 100+ sp when Phalanx gets a rank up strike. When target gets stunned by the shock spikes you can also allow yourself a couple of quick slash &amp; stabs before returning to the safety of your raised shield cycle.  <br /> <br />I noticed just a small decrease in total SP after a fight but it was made up by being able to kill a red or orange and move to the next one without delay and kill it and keep going. Vs greens and blues slashing like crazy you end up a bit hurt, out of stamina and have a higher downtime between fights. </div>
