      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig"> <br />However it does not change the SP gain that much. Thing is, the SP you get is also tied to the damage you do. I almost always get 100+ sp when Phalanx gets a rank up strike. When target gets stunned by the shock spikes you can also allow yourself a couple of quick slash &amp; stabs before returning to the safety of your raised shield cycle. <br /></div></div> <br /> <br />I very much disagree with this, mainly because the scaling on rank sp is not linear based on damage, or at least not that I've noticed.  For instance, I can spam light slash for 80ish damage a pop and recieve 60-70 rank sp when it procs.  Then I can use phalanx or a WS for 200+ damage, and see maybe 100-110 rank sp.  If you factor it out, it becomes glaringly apparent that using attacks that do the LEAST amount of damage repeatedly will net you more rank sp.  Unfortunately I have not tested this extensively so it is all just from observation.  On this note, using defender can also help in gaining SP, as it reduces your attack value (and since the equation for SP doesn't appear to be linear, it makes less difference). <br /> <br />Also, I have absolutely ZERO problems holding hate.  In a group, my strategy is:  Still Precision, engage, Light Slash, Guard, Provoke/Taunt, Phalanx, and then just light slash spam.  It has given me consistenly better returns than just spamming phalanx.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://somethingwitty.mmoguildsites.com" rel="external nofollow" title="somethingwitty.mmoguildsites.com">Something Witty- FFXIV linkshell</a></div></div>
