      <div class="msgContentFrame">Actually, what you see of the spell being cast and shield raised is the very 'stuck in animation' issue I was talking about. <br /> <br />You cannot do two things at the same time. The game does not allow it. What you see is you casting the protect spell and it gets CAST but your character takes a second and a half longer to finish the animation of 'cast protect'. You had pressed Guard while the protect spell was being cast so it was Queued. So, on the server's side, you had your shield raised already but on your screen you didnt see it (you were seing the ending of the protect cast animation). When the protect animation ends, your client usually 'warps' into raised shield position without showing you the 'raising shield' animation since it was already done and past. Only times you get to see it is if your character is not being hit, evading or being involved in any other animation. <br /> <br />It seems that in general, you see the animations of what the server reports as a 'done thing' 2 to 3 seconds later. <br /> <br />In my video you can see a clear example of this happening. The very first phalanx attack I do on the mob shows the 'stuck on animation' issue. <br /> <br />At 0:48 my character was swinging weapon while shield raised and blocked the attack. <br />At 0:50 it finishes the attack animation and returns to shield raised position. <br />At 0:50 I had also pressed Phalanx (you can see it on my stamina bar being selected). <br />At 0:51 to 0:52 it animates the start of Phalanx with the light effect popping up. <br />At 0:54 we see phalanx attack damage hit the mob and light go off. At the same time my shield drops. <br /> <br />But we do not see the Phalanx swing attack animation. Why? Because somewhere around O:50 and 0:52 my shield guard dropped and the server sent the order to my client to animate the shield drop. So my client 'skips' the phalanx animation to lower the shield. <br /> <br />The same issue happens when you are attacking. The game will skip the lower shield animation to do the attack animation. It will skip the lower shield animation to do the 'ouch i got hit' animation (or the animation done when you take a TP move hit).  <br /> <br />And this sucks big time because you cant reliably keep pace with your shield guard. Its even worse when you have 2 or more mobs on you. That is when Parry comes into play.  <br /> <br /></div>
