      <div class="msgContentFrame">Not really.  I realize that Provoke doesn't work like it did in ffxi.  It is easily noticeable by the chat log &quot;The effect of Provoke has worn off.&quot;  However, what I have noticed is that if you DO voke and then consistently attack it, you can be severely outdamaged by other classes and yet still maintain hate.  In multiple mob battles this becomes exceedingly more difficult obviously, but with only 1 mob I have never had an issue.  As for what I'm fighting, it has been a variety of things.  Jellyfish in Cassiopeia at 18-22, crabs at 22+, wolves in coerthas, etc...  The battles aren't lasting an exceedingly long time, but I'd say about 30s each on average and we are chaining them as fast as we can get to them. <br /> <br />Stamina-wise, I 100% agree with you.  Phalanx is the single most stamina efficient move in the game... because it costs none and while the animation plays you actually RECOVER stam.  I have yet to try the method you speak of so I really can't comment on it.  I do find it intriguing that different WS seem to give different amounts of skillup, as I had not really noticed that.  I did however notice that if you use a WS with an added effect (like Howling Vortex), you can actually gain sp on both the WS AND the added effect procs.   <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov  4th 2010  2:35pm by BartelX </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://somethingwitty.mmoguildsites.com" rel="external nofollow" title="somethingwitty.mmoguildsites.com">Something Witty- FFXIV linkshell</a></div></div>
