      <div class="msgContentFrame">You should add Feint to that list.  It has the same stamina and tp cost as phalanx but does slightly less damage.   <br /> <br />However, the main benefit is that this attack NEVER misses.  You can even use it after a whiffed phalanx.  When you party with other gladiators or aren't necessarily required to hold hate full time, Feint is the ONLY reactionary ability you can use when not tanking. <br /> <br />Feint feels mandatory for any melee job due to how much it increases your damage output and accuracy while lowering stamina costs.  Between feint and phalanx, there isn't enough time to use any other reactionary abilities because I whiff my own attacks and block enemy attacks far more often than I parry or evade them. <br /> <br />I usually prep for fights with Still Precision and/or Invigorate for a boost in acc and TP (both abilities are on a close recast timer as Gladiator).  Then &gt; Light Slash &gt; Provoke and go into a cycle of attacking, guarding, and using feint/phalanx whenever possible.  Usually, this is all that's necessary to finish off a mob but it also keeps the stamina bar high enough to throw in those high-stamina abilities when you really need them.</div>
